The Dominican Republic[a] is a North American country located on the island
of Hispaniola in the Greater Antilles of the Caribbean Sea in the North
Atlantic Ocean. It shares a maritime border with Puerto Rico to the east
and a land border with Haiti to the west, occupying the eastern five-eighths
of Hispaniola which, along with Saint Martin, is one of only two islands
in the Caribbean shared by two sovereign states.[15][16] In the Antilles, the
country is the second-largest nation by area after Cuba at 48,671 square.